{
  "texts": [
    "However, due to the operating principles of traditional protections, there is a tradeoff between speed and false positive detections.",
    "Machine learning algorithms can mitigate this by leveraging different detection principles and input features that can help do an early detection of the fault (Azhar et al., 2022).",
    "The design of a protective relay system should give priority to simplicity and straightforwardness, while still achieving the intended objectives.",
    "Each additional unit or component that enhances protection but is not essential to the basic protection requirements should be carefully considered.",
    "Each added element introduces a potential source of problems and increased maintenance."
  ]
}